   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from entsoe import EntsoePandasClient\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "plt.rcParams[\"figure.figsize\"] = (12, 5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Paramètres : période d'étude et frontières\n",
    "\n",
    "On définit la liste des bidding zones voisines de la France. Attention :\n",
    "- L'Allemagne est en zone couplée `DE_LU` (Allemagne-Luxembourg).\n",
    "- L'Italie côté FR est la zone `IT_NORD`.\n",
    "- La Suisse `CH` n'est pas couplée au marché unique européen, mais les données existent."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ⚠️ Remplace par ton token ENTSO-E\n",
    "API_KEY = \"TON_TOKEN_ENTSOE_ICI\"\n",
    "\n",
    "client = EntsoePandasClient(api_key=API_KEY)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Période d'analyse (par ex. l'année 2024)\n",
    "start = pd.Timestamp(\"2024-01-01\", tz=\"Europe/Paris\")\n",
    "end   = pd.Timestamp(\"2024-12-31\", tz=\"Europe/Paris\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Frontières françaises : (code_voisin, libellé)\n",
    "NEIGHBORS = {\n",
    "    \"DE_LU\":   \"Allemagne-Luxembourg\",\n",
    "    \"BE\":      \"Belgique\",\n",
    "    \"CH\":      \"Suisse\",\n",
    "    \"IT_NORD\": \"Italie Nord\",\n",
    "    \"ES\":      \"Espagne\",\n",
    "    \"GB\":      \"Grande-Bretagne\",\n",
    "}\n",
    "FR = \"FR\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Récupération des prix day-ahead\n",
    "\n",
    "Le prix spot day-ahead est l'information clé : tant qu'une interconnexion n'est pas saturée, le market coupling égalise les prix des deux côtés. Une **différence de prix non nulle = congestion**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "prices = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Prix France\n",
    "prices[FR] = client.query_day_ahead_prices(FR, start=start, end=end)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Prix voisins\n",
    "for zone in NEIGHBORS:\n",
    "    print(f\"Téléchargement prix {zone}...\")\n",
    "    prices[zone] = client.query_day_ahead_prices(zone, start=start, end=end)\n",
    "\n",
    "# On assemble tout dans un DataFrame horaire\n",
    "df_prices = pd.concat(prices, axis=1)\n",
    "df_prices.columns = df_prices.columns.get_level_values(0)\n",
    "df_prices = df_prices.resample(\"H\").mean()  # certaines zones publient au pas 15 min\n",
    "df_prices.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Statistiques descriptives des prix par zone (€/MWh)\n",
    "df_prices.describe().round(1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Indicateur 1 — Spreads de prix FR vs voisins\n",
    "\n",
    "Pour chaque frontière, on calcule $\\text{spread}_t = P^{voisin}_t - P^{FR}_t$.\n",
    "- Spread > 0 → la France est moins chère (on devrait exporter vers le voisin).\n",
    "- Spread < 0 → la France est plus chère (on devrait importer).\n",
    "- |spread| > seuil (par ex. 1 €/MWh) → marché **non couplé** = congestion."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "spreads = pd.DataFrame({z: df_prices[z] - df_prices[FR] for z in NEIGHBORS})\n",
    "spreads.describe().round(2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Distribution des spreads\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(14, 7), sharex=True)\n",
    "for ax, (zone, label) in zip(axes.flat, NEIGHBORS.items()):\n",
    "    spreads[zone].hist(bins=80, ax=ax, color=\"steelblue\")\n",
    "    ax.axvline(0, color=\"red\", lw=1)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f\"{label} - FR\")\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel(\"Spread (€/MWh)\")\n",
    "plt.suptitle(\"Distribution des spreads de prix day-ahead\", y=1.02)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Indicateur 2 — Taux de découplage de marché\n",
    "\n",
    "Part des heures où |spread| > 1 €/MWh : c'est la part des heures où l'interconnexion **sature** (les prix ne convergent pas)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "SEUIL = 1.0  # €/MWh, tolérance numérique\n",
    "\n",
    "decoupling = (spreads.abs() > SEUIL).mean() * 100\n",
    "decoupling = decoupling.sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "decoupling = decoupling.rename(\"% heures découplées\").to_frame()\n",
    "decoupling[\"Frontière\"] = decoupling.index.map(NEIGHBORS)\n",
    "decoupling[[\"Frontière\", \"% heures découplées\"]].round(1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ax = decoupling[\"% heures découplées\"].plot(kind=\"bar\", color=\"darkorange\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"% des heures avec |spread| > 1 €/MWh\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Part des heures de congestion par frontière (FR vs voisin)\")\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels([NEIGHBORS[z] for z in decoupling.index], rotation=30, ha=\"right\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Récupération des flux physiques transfrontaliers\n",
    "\n",
    "Les flux physiques mesurent l'électricité qui circule réellement sur les lignes. On va construire un **flux net** = export FR→voisin − import voisin→FR."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "flows_net = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for zone, label in NEIGHBORS.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"Téléchargement flux FR<->{zone}...\")\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        exp = client.query_crossborder_flows(FR, zone, start=start, end=end)\n",
    "        imp = client.query_crossborder_flows(zone, FR, start=start, end=end)\n",
    "        flows_net[zone] = (exp.resample(\"H\").mean() - imp.resample(\"H\").mean())\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"  ⚠️ Erreur sur {zone} : {e}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "df_flows = pd.DataFrame(flows_net)\n",
    "# Convention : > 0 = export net de FR vers le voisin\n",
    "df_flows.describe().round(0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Bilan énergétique annuel : exports nets de la France (TWh)\n",
    "bilan = (df_flows.sum() / 1e6).round(2).rename(\"Export net FR (TWh)\")\n",
    "bilan = bilan.to_frame()\n",
    "bilan[\"Frontière\"] = bilan.index.map(NEIGHBORS)\n",
    "bilan[[\"Frontière\", \"Export net FR (TWh)\"]].sort_values(\"Export net FR (TWh)\", ascending=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Indicateur 3 — Taux d'utilisation des capacités (NTC)\n",
    "\n",
    "La **Net Transfer Capacity** (NTC) est la capacité commerciale offerte au marché day-ahead. On compare le flux réel à la NTC pour mesurer le taux de saturation.\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\text{utilisation}_t = \\frac{|\\text{flux net}_t|}{\\text{NTC}_t}$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ntc = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for zone, label in NEIGHBORS.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"Téléchargement NTC FR<->{zone}...\")\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        ntc_exp = client.query_net_transfer_capacity_dayahead(FR, zone, start=start, end=end)\n",
    "        ntc_imp = client.query_net_transfer_capacity_dayahead(zone, FR, start=start, end=end)\n",
    "        ntc[zone] = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "            \"NTC_export\": ntc_exp.resample(\"H\").mean(),\n",
    "            \"NTC_import\": ntc_imp.resample(\"H\").mean(),\n",
    "        })\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"  ⚠️ Erreur sur {zone} : {e}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Taux d'utilisation moyen par frontière\n",
    "util_rates = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for zone in NEIGHBORS:\n",
    "    if zone not in ntc:\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    flux = df_flows[zone]\n",
    "    # On prend la NTC dans la bonne direction selon le signe du flux\n",
    "    capa = np.where(flux >= 0,\n",
    "                    ntc[zone][\"NTC_export\"].reindex(flux.index),\n",
    "                    ntc[zone][\"NTC_import\"].reindex(flux.index))\n",
    "    util = np.abs(flux.values) / np.where(capa > 0, capa, np.nan)\n",
    "    util_rates[zone] = pd.Series(util, index=flux.index)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_util = pd.DataFrame(util_rates)\n",
    "df_util.describe().round(2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Part des heures avec utilisation > 95 % (interco quasi saturée)\n",
    "saturation = (df_util > 0.95).mean() * 100\n",
    "saturation = saturation.sort_values(ascending=False).rename(\"% heures saturées\")\n",
    "print(saturation.round(1))\n",
    "\n",
    "ax = saturation.plot(kind=\"bar\", color=\"crimson\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"% des heures à utilisation > 95 %\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Saturation physique des interconnexions FR\")\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels([NEIGHBORS[z] for z in saturation.index], rotation=30, ha=\"right\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Indicateur 4 — Rente de congestion\n",
    "\n",
    "La rente de congestion correspond au revenu collecté par les GRT (RTE et son voisin) lorsque l'interconnexion sature :\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{Rente}_t = |P_t^{voisin} - P_t^{FR}| \\times |\\text{flux}_t|$$\n",
    "\n",
    "C'est un proxy classique du coût économique de la congestion."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rente = pd.DataFrame(index=df_flows.index)\n",
    "for zone in NEIGHBORS:\n",
    "    if zone not in df_flows.columns:\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    spread_h = spreads[zone].reindex(df_flows.index)\n",
    "    rente[zone] = spread_h.abs() * df_flows[zone].abs()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Total annuel en M€\n",
    "rente_annuelle = (rente.sum() / 1e6).round(1).rename(\"Rente (M€)\")\n",
    "rente_annuelle = rente_annuelle.to_frame()\n",
    "rente_annuelle[\"Frontière\"] = rente_annuelle.index.map(NEIGHBORS)\n",
    "rente_annuelle = rente_annuelle[[\"Frontière\", \"Rente (M€)\"]].sort_values(\"Rente (M€)\", ascending=False)\n",
    "rente_annuelle"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ax = rente_annuelle.set_index(\"Frontière\")[\"Rente (M€)\"].plot(kind=\"bar\", color=\"seagreen\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Rente de congestion (M€)\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Rente de congestion annuelle par frontière FR\")\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=30, ha=\"right\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Analyse temporelle : quand congestionne-t-on le plus ?\n",
    "\n",
    "On regarde si les congestions sont concentrées sur certaines heures (pointe / creux) ou certains mois."
